    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.004/3–150</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-01">March 1,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had a conversation with David Sarnoff<note n="1" xml:id="d127fn1">Chairman of
                        the Radio Corporation of America.</note> the other day, regarding the
                    exploitation of the Voice of America.</p>
                <p>He suggested a committee, consisting of himself, Senator McMahon,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d127fn2">Senator Brien McMahon of Connecticut.</note> Senator
                        McFarland<note n="3" xml:id="d127fn3">Senator Ernest W. McFarland of
                        Arizona.</note>—on account of his Chairmanship of the Subcommittee on
                    Communications in the Senate, Under Secretary of Defense Stephen Early, and
                    Assistant Secretary of State Barrett, to look into the problem of improving the
                    Voice of America.</p>
                <p>I wish you would consider that, and we will discuss it when you come over
                        tomorrow.<note n="4" xml:id="d127fn4">A marginal handwritten notation on the
                        source text indicates that Secretary of State Acheson discussed this
                        memorandum with President Truman on March 2; see also Assistant Secretary
                        Barrett’s memorandum of March 2 to Secretary Acheson, <hi rend="italic"
                            >infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">arry</hi>] S. T[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ruman</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
